    <div class="field field-name-field-ww-summary field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>In part one (<a href="http://webwash.net/node/157">How to Store Addresses in Drupal 7 Using Location Module</a>), we configured <a href="http://drupal.org/project/location">Location</a> to store and geocode addresses.</p>

<p>We used "Location CCK" that ships with Location, to define a custom address field on the Article content type. This field allows us to enter in a postal address and then Location stores the address and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geocoding">geocodes</a> it. Now we need to display the address in an actual map.</p>

<p>In this tutorial, we'll use two modules to create our map: <a href="http://drupal.org/project/views">Views</a> to build a block and <a href="http://drupal.org/project/gmap">GMap</a> for the actual map.</p>

<p>The map that we'll create will be fairly basic. The block will only be visible on the article page if an address is entered in.</p>
